COPS are offering a reward of up to R50Â 000 for any valuable information that can lead to the arrest and subsequent conviction of the killers of a Ward councillor. The cops in Tubatse outside Burgersfort in Limpopo are searching for the killers of a ward councillor Thabang Maupa. Maupa was gunned down by unknown men at about 19:00 on Monday night. His wife was also injured in the shooting. Police spokesperson Brigadier Motlafela Mojapelo said the brutal killing took place at the couple's liquor Restaurant at Ribacross next to the R37 Road. He said Maupa, aged 42, allegedly arrived at this place to assist his wife to close the shop. After closing, the couple was still in their car when an unknown suspect who was on foot, suddenly started firing shots at their vehicle. "During this fatal attack, the deceased was hit several times and died on the scene. His wife, aged 40, sustained injuries after she was also hit by stray bullets," said Mojapelo. He said the motive for this killing is unknown at this stage, but police have opened cases of murder and attempted murder and investigations are underway. Anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the suspect(s) is requested to contact Colonel Makhathini Ngele at 082 573 3645, the police toll-free number 0860010111, the Sms Crime Line 32211or the nearest police station.